#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -euo pipefail

cat <<'EOF'
NovaArch first boot notes
------------------------
- Logitech G HUB is not available on Linux; use piper/solaar/openrgb alternatives.
- For Logitech wheel tuning, try oversteer.
- Lian Li SL Wireless LCD Linux control may be partial/unofficial.
- Live session uses KDE Plasma (SDDM autologin as user live). Connect Wi‑Fi, then Welcome → Launch Installer (archinstall).
- Meta (Windows) opens the launcher; System Settings has Display, Appearance, Bluetooth, and power.
- Choose animated scene with: novaarch-wallpaper-selector
- NovaArch Control Center can auto-open on login (toggle inside it).
- Shortcut: add a custom shortcut in System Settings → Shortcuts, or use the application launcher.
- If Bluetooth/Wi-Fi need reset: sudo novaarch-wireless-repair
EOF
